 <paragraph index="71" node_type="writer">Environment Parameters</paragraph>
 <paragraph index="72" node_type="writer">To be able to simulate an environment and to train our RL agent, we need to first set values to our constant parameters and initialize our simulated environment using those values. These parameters should not change across different training phases and experiments.</paragraph>
 <paragraph index="74" node_type="writer">Number of consumers: NUM_CONSUMERS = 50</paragraph>
 <paragraph index="75" node_type="writer">Number of periods: EPISODE_LENGTH = 100</paragraph>
 <paragraph index="77" node_type="writer">Hotelling line parameters</paragraph>
 <paragraph index="78" node_type="writer">HOTELLING_LEFT = 0.0</paragraph>
 <paragraph index="79" node_type="writer">HOTELLING_RIGHT = 1.0</paragraph>
 <paragraph index="80" node_type="writer">FIRM_A_LOCATION = 0.0</paragraph>
 <paragraph index="81" node_type="writer">FIRM_B_LOCATION = 1.0</paragraph>
 <paragraph index="83" node_type="writer">Economic parameters</paragraph>
 <paragraph index="84" node_type="writer">t : TRANSPORTATION_COST = 1.0</paragraph>
 <paragraph index="85" node_type="writer">V: BASE_VALUE = 10.0</paragraph>
 <paragraph index="87" node_type="writer">Consumer location</paragraph>
 <paragraph index="88" node_type="writer">consumers location are randomly sampled from a uniform distribution</paragraph>
